No. 7

Commercial Agency of the United States of America at Sierra Leone
6th December 1866

Sir

It become my painful duty to report to the Department the death of William Powers a citizen of Boston Mass, and late master of the bark "Helen Mania" of Salem Mass. I took an inventory of his effects and forward by the "Helen Mania" to his employees and authenticated copy of it.

Before dying he made his well which he left in charge of his Counqre

I have the honor to be
Sir
Your most obdt Servant
Henry Rider
U.S. Con Agent

Hon. W.H. Seward
Secretary of State